This paper discusses the application of ethical concepts in machine learning, specifically in subset selection problems. The most relevant sub-category for this topic is likely cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on developing metrics for evaluating fairness in ML settings. Additionally, the paper touches on social choice methods, which could fall under cs.CY (Computational Social Choice). The concepts of diversity and inclusion are also relevant to the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social informatics (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for privacy violations in subset selection, which could fall under the sub-category of cryptography (cs.CR).
